cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with mammogram classification using deep convolutional features and multi-instance learning. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning and end-to-end training also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a possible sub-category. The paper specifically deals with mammograms, which is a type of medical imaging, indicating the medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep multi-instance networks suggests neural networks (cs.NE) as another possible sub-category.
